'''Țuțora''' is a commune in [[Iași County]], [[Romania]]. It is composed of three villages: Chiperești, Oprișeni and Țuțora. In 2002, it had a population of 2,119. The [[Battle of Cecora (1620)|Battle of Țuțora]] took place here in 1620.
